.th TDIR VI 19-March-1980
.sh NAME
tdir \*- list tape directories
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd tdir
[ \*-b ] [ \*-\c
.it unit
] [
.it count
]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Tdir
outputs directory listings of magtape in several formats.
.it Tdir
can identify
tp format, DOS-PIP format, and XAP picture
format with or without a header.
Tape labels are also recognized.
If the files on the tape
do not belong to the above mentioned formats then the message
"unknown format" is output.
.it Tdir
lists any tape directory contents until a double file mark is found.
Finally, the total number of files read is output.
The numerical suffix of the program name
determines the default unit number.
If the last character of the program name is not a digit the
default 0 is assumed.
The optional unit parameter (preceded by a dash \*-)
can override the default tape unit number.
An optional decimal parameter represents the maximum
number of files to be processed.
In its absence,
.it tdir
lists directories for all files.
The optional parameter \*-b provides a briefer listing format.
.sh DIAGNOSTICS
.it Tdir
stops listing the tape directories
if it is unable to find /usr/mdec/mboot and outputs an appropriate message.
